Including Plots

You can also embed plots, for example:

Note that the echo = FALSE parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.

## Reading layer `MP14_SUBZONE_WEB_PL' from data source `D:\GitHub\Prof Kam R Mardown tmap\data\data.gov' using driver `ESRI Shapefile'
## Simple feature collection with 323 features and 15 fields
## geometry type:  MULTIPOLYGON
## dimension:      XY
## bbox:           xmin: 2667.538 ymin: 15748.72 xmax: 56396.44 ymax: 50256.33
## epsg (SRID):    NA
## proj4string:    +proj=tmerc +lat_0=1.366666666666667 +lon_0=103.8333333333333 +k=1 +x_0=28001.642 +y_0=38744.572 +datum=WGS84 +units=m +no_defs
popagsex <- read_csv("data/AttributeTables/respopagsex2000to2017.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   PA = col_character(),
##   SZ = col_character(),
##   AG = col_character(),
##   Sex = col_character(),
##   Pop = col_integer(),
##   Time = col_integer()
## )
popagsex2017_male <- popagsex %>%
filter(Sex == "Males") %>%
filter(Time == 2017) %>%
spread(AG, Pop) %>%
mutate(YOUNG = `0_to_4`+`5_to_9`+`10_to_14`+
`15_to_19`+`20_to_24`) %>%
mutate(`ECONOMY ACTIVE` = rowSums(.[9:13])+
rowSums(.[15:17]))%>%
mutate(`AGED`=rowSums(.[18:22])) %>%
mutate(`TOTAL`=rowSums(.[5:22])) %>%
mutate(`DEPENDENCY` = (`YOUNG` + `AGED`)
/`ECONOMY ACTIVE`) %>%
mutate_at(.vars = vars(PA, SZ), .funs = funs(toupper))
mpsz_agemale2017 <- left_join(mpsz, popagsex2017_male,
by = c("SUBZONE_N" = "SZ"))
## Warning: Column `SUBZONE_N`/`SZ` joining factor and character vector,
## coercing into character vector
qtm(mpsz_agemale2017, fill = "DEPENDENCY")

tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017) +
tm_polygons()

tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017) +
tm_polygons("DEPENDENCY")

tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017) +
tm_fill("DEPENDENCY")

tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017)+
tm_fill("DEPENDENCY") +
tm_borders(alpha = 0.8, lty="dashed")

tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017)+
tm_fill("DEPENDENCY",
n = 5,
style = "quantile") +
tm_borders(alpha = 0.5)

tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017)+
tm_fill("DEPENDENCY",
n = 5,
style = "equal") +
tm_borders(alpha = 0.5)

tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017)+
tm_fill("DEPENDENCY",
style = "quantile",
palette = "Greens") +
tm_borders(alpha = 0.5)

tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017)+
tm_fill("DEPENDENCY",
style = "quantile",
palette = "-Greens") +
tm_borders(alpha = 0.5)

tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017)+
tm_fill("DEPENDENCY",
style = "quantile",
palette = "Blues",
legend.hist = TRUE,
legend.is.portrait = TRUE,
legend.hist.z = 0.1) +
tm_layout(legend.height = 0.45,
legend.width = 0.35,
legend.outside = TRUE,
legend.position = c("right", "bottom"),
frame = FALSE) +
tm_borders(alpha = 0.5)

tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017)+
tm_fill("DEPENDENCY",
style = "quantile",
palette = "-Greens") +
tm_borders(alpha = 0.5) +
tmap_style("classic")
## tmap style set to "classic"

##note: tmap_style will override most settings, such as font type

tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017)+
tm_fill("DEPENDENCY",
style = "quantile",
palette = "Blues",
title = "No. of persons") +
tm_layout(main.title = "Distribution of Dependency Ratio \nby Planning Subzone",
main.title.position = "center",
main.title.size = 1.2,
legend.height = 0.45,
legend.width = 0.35,
frame = TRUE) +
tm_borders(alpha = 0.5) +
tm_compass(type="8star", size = 2) +
tm_scale_bar() +
tm_grid() +
tm_credits("Source: Planning Sub-zone boundary from Urban Redevelopment
Authorithy (URA)\n and Population data from Department of Statistics DOS",
position = c("left", "bottom"))

tmap_style("white")
## tmap style set to "white"
tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017)+
tm_fill(c("YOUNG", "AGED"),
style = "equal",
palette = "Blues") +
tm_layout(legend.position = c("right", "bottom")) +
tm_borders(alpha = 0.5) +
tmap_style("white")
## tmap style set to "white"

tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017)+
tm_polygons(c("DEPENDENCY","DEPENDENCY"),
style = c("equal", "quantile"),
palette = list("Blues","Blues")) +
tm_layout(legend.position = c("right", "bottom"))

tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017) +
tm_fill("DEPENDENCY",
style = "quantile",
palette = "Blues",
thres.poly = 0) +
tm_facets(by="REGION_N",
free.coords=TRUE,
drop.shapes=TRUE) +
tm_layout(legend.show = FALSE,
title.position = c("center", "center"),
title.size = 20) +
tm_borders(alpha = 0.5)
## Warning: The argument drop.shapes has been renamed to drop.units, and is
## therefore deprecated

youngmap <- tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017)+
tm_polygons("YOUNG",
style = "quantile",
palette = "Blues")
agedmap <- tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017)+
tm_polygons("AGED",
style = "quantile",
palette = "Blues")
tmap_arrange(youngmap, agedmap, asp=1, ncol=2)

tm_shape(mpsz_agemale2017[mpsz_agemale2017$REGION_N=="CENTRAL REGION", ])+
tm_fill("DEPENDENCY",
style = "quantile",
palette = "Blues",
legend.hist = TRUE,
legend.is.portrait = TRUE,
legend.hist.z = 0.1) +
tm_layout(legend.outside = TRUE,
legend.height = 0.45,
legend.width = 5.0,
legend.position = c("right", "bottom"),
frame = FALSE) +
tm_borders(alpha = 0.5)

tmap_mode("view")
## tmap mode set to interactive viewing
mpsz_wgs84 <- st_transform(mpsz_agemale2017, 4326)
tm_shape(mpsz_wgs84)+
tm_fill("DEPENDENCY",
n = 6,
style = "quantile",
palette = "Blues") +
tm_borders(alpha = 0.5)

## to switch tmap mode back to plotting mode, running the following code chunk:

tmap_mode("plot")
## tmap mode set to plotting
